New Project Setup

step 1  :
    install  package-log  ->     npm init -y
    install express  ->  npm install express
    install nodemon  ->  npm install --save-dev nodemon
    install .env   ->  npm install dotenv
    install mongoose  ->  npm install mongoose
    install cors  ->  npm install cors





step 2 :

    create  index.js on project file  inside






    notes :

            keep file structure
                project-name/
                    ├── node_modules/
                    ├── public/         # Static files (images, CSS, etc.)
                    ├── public/   
                    ├──  src/ 
                    ├── package.json            # Environment variables
                    ├── .env
                    └── .gitignore

step 3  :

    add script  in package.json("package.json is automatically created for install  follwing  step 1") so  add this  2 script

    "scripts": {
        "start": "node index.js",
        "dev": "nodemon index.js"
    }
